<HEADLINE>Not so generous</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974913600</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ARITHMETIC was never my strongpoint, but even I can calculate that the
``generous'' handout on law and order by our dedicated Secretary of State (at
the expense of virtually everything else within his deliverance) amounts to
fewer than 2!s additional policemen per annum within each Scottish constituency
over the three years' ``assistance''.
Methinks even Mr Forsyth's pathetically minuscule band of fellow-Tory MPs will
be somewhat under-impressed, not least Allan Stewart, battling away in what,
following April's Unitary Council elections, has become a marginal Eastwood.
Here, the ``benefit'' amounts to fewer than 0.12 extra bobbies per ward for
each of the years!
Bill Wilde,
86 Montgomery Street,
Eaglesham.
</TEXT>
