<TEXT>
A CAR bomb killed at least 15 people and wounded more than 40 in a suburb of
the Algerian capital Algiers today.
The booby-trapped vehicle was parked near a cafe in Ain Naadja suburb. Several
of the wounded were in serious condition, state-run media reported, adding that
Interior Minister Mustapha Ben Mensour had rushed to the scene.
The bomb was the most bloody attack since last month's presidential election
which the authorities saw as a first step to ending nearly four years of
conflict with Muslim fundamentalists seeking to overthrow them.
