<HEADLINE>Leeson appeals</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974913664</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Singapore, Tuesday
FORMER futures trader Nick Leeson, above, whose disastrous dealings helped
bring down Barings bank, lodged notice of appeal today against his jail
sentence for cheating.
The appeal was against the six-year sentence he received on one of two charges
to which he pleaded guilty this month. He had been sentenced to a further six
months on the other charge. Today was the final day that Leeson could file the
appeal and it was submitted less than an hour before the deadline.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
