<HEADLINE>Gould is confident</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974913675</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WALES
WELSH manager Bobby Gould rubbed his hands together and smiled broadly at the
prospect of locking horns with Holland and Belgium in Group 7.
With minnows San Marino and Euro '96 finalists Turkey also in their five-strong
group, Gould said: ``It's such a great, great opportunity. Not only are the
games against Holland and Belgium ones we can look forward to financially, but
they're also games we really believe we can win.''
The Belgians are far from unfamiliar opponents, with meetings in the qualifying
tournaments for the 1992 European Championships, in which Wales picked up three
points out of four, and the 1994 World Cup, when each side won their home game
2-0.
But Wales have lost all three of their previous games against the Dutch.
</TEXT>
