<HEADLINE>Fear of the unknown</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974913677</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NORTHERN IRELAND
MANAGER Bryan Hamilton reacted with a smile and a joke after hearing that his
country had been paired alongside Germany and Portugal in the qualifying draw.
Hamilton's homework began immediately, as he was summarising for BBC Radio 5
Live on Portugal's match against England at Wembley. The six-country group is
completed by Armenia, Albania, and the Ukraine.
``I have a choice,'' he said. ``I either throw myself off the twin towers or I
plan for the play-offs - I think I will plan for the play-offs. To be honest,
Portugal are a side who always put you under a lot of pressure. Germany will be
tough, but it is a great tie as well.
``However, I'm more worried about Armenia, Albania, and the Ukraine. At least I
know something about the other two.''
</TEXT>
