<TEXT>
REPUBLIC OF IRELAND
JACK Charlton greeted news of the draw with optimism - even though his team
have to play in one of the six-nation groups.
He said: ``Romania are the only team there that you would say had excellent
quality. Even so, I believe that many of their top players are coming towards
the end of their careers.
``We remember them from the penalty shoot-out in the World Cup finals in Italy,
and they also did well in America, of course.
``To me, it looks like them or us to win the group because there are no other
teams we know we can't beat. It will be a case of not making a slip against the
smaller sides. In a group of equal standings you can often recover from the odd
mistake but it is unlikely in this one.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
