<TEXT>
NAIRN striker John Davidson has been banned for nine games after having
received three red cards in one match. Davidson was ordered off against
Fraserburgh a week ago for a second bookable offence.
He picked up a second red card from referee David Patience for swearing as he
walked from the park, and a third for challenging the official after the game,
although he claims he never spoke to the referee at that point.
County manager Harry McFadden said: ``John has been banned for exceeding the
disciplinary points level, not for bringing the game into disrepute. He
maintains he wasn't swearing at the referee, but was unhappy at the foul being
awarded.''
Davidson has been suspended for two games for the red cards, three additional
games for the hat trick, and four for passing the points threshold. The player
has now threatened to give up the game for the rest of the season.
``By the time the ban is over my fitness will have dropped and there will only
be four or five games left to play,'' he said. ``I don't know if it would be
worth carrying on.''
q THE referee's jurisdiction lasts from the moment he arrives at the ground
until he leaves.
Any player guilty of misconduct - before or after the 90 minutes - is subject
to a referee's report to the SFA.
