<TEXT>
PAUL Bernard's wish is to follow Eoin Jess into the Scottish side for the
European Championship finals next summer. The midfield man has marvelled at the
skills of his Aberdeen team-mate since moving from Oldham.
Bernard, who already has two caps from Scotland's Far East tour last summer,
said yesterday: ``I knew Eoin from our days together with Scotland's Under-21
side and always respected his ability.
``Since joining Aberdeen I can see why he is back in the Scotland side. He is
certainly justifying his place.''
Meanwhile, Dons' captain Stewart McKimmie returns from suspension tonight for
the rescheduled match against Kilmarnock at Pittodrie, which was abandoned last
Wednesday after floodlight failure, but Scott Booth and John Inglis are ruled
out through injury.
Kilmarnock's Tom Black is almost certainly out, suffering from tonsillitis.
