<TEXT>
IT was reported on December 8 that six cows had been seized by trading
standards officers in a BSE-related investigation. It transpires that the
beasts were sold at Lanark having been declared free of the disease. The six
cows then being transported for slaughter at Biggar were not the same ones but
carried the same paperwork.
The next time you bite into some British beef ask yourself if it came from a
sane or a mad cow. If the Lanark incident is anything to so on you will never
know if your bit of beef was mad or a potential PhD student.
Michael Nugent,
17 Dorchester Avenue,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
