<HEADLINE>Drink and driving</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974913697</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
W M FRASER is correct to question the witch-hunt for drunk drivers (December
11). I also would welcome a ``serious and impartial'' investigation into the
hard facts of road injuries and deaths.
There can be no doubt that the vast majority of accidents are caused by bad
driving when sober. It would therefore seem to make more sense to target
incompetent and careless drivers all year round.
The current campaign may indeed be costing rather than saving lives.
Robert Durward,
Netherton House,
Biggar.
</TEXT>
