Rowing
HENLEY Regatta chiefs yesterday announced sweeping changes to their
qualification rules in a bid to prevent powerful regional and university clubs
pot-hunting in events designed for ordinary club and student crews.
The Thames Cup will be restricted to club crews, with all crews seeking
international representation barred. Only two former internationalists,
including lightweights, will be allowed per entry.
The Temple Cup will be restricted to student club crews, with Oxford and
Cambridge Blues and equivalent oarsmen from other institutions both at home and
overseas barred.
Also ruled out will be senior and under-23 internationalists, World Student
Games competitors, and previous winners of Henley events for seniors.
