<TEXT>
BUILT at a cost of #1.2m, a new 22,000 sq ft extension to the hose and ducting
factory of Flexible Ducting Ltd at Cloberfield, Milngavie, has already resulted
in an increase in jobs and is regarded as both boosting production and
strengthening the firm's position as the leading manufacturer of flexible
ducting within the United Kingdom.
``We regard this investment as vital in our efforts to further strengthen our
UK position and to heighten our presence in Europe,'' said Mr Phil Battle,
director and general manager of Flexible Ducting Ltd.
``Apart from giving us the capacity to introduce new products, with the
benefits of additional warehousing space we will be improving the efficiency of
our service to distributors.
``It is also very satisfying to be able to secure the future for our workforce
and create additional employment for this area.'' The new extension, built by
John Dickie Construction, which includes both warehouse and office space, will
allow the company to create additional manufacturing space within the previous
main site and will boost overall production in heating, ventilation, domestic
appliance and industrial production.
Proud of its slogan ``Quality by Design'', Flexible Ducting Ltd, which employs
140 people, is a subsidiary of Smiths Industries. Four years ago it was the
first company in its industrial sector to achieve accreditation to BS 5750 Part
1/ISO 900l for the quality of its manufacturing systems. Heavy investments
backed by commitment to quality of product have been features throughout its
history.
Over 40% of the company's output is destined for use overseas.
When established over 34 years ago, the company was originally owned by the
Maclellan Rubber group. Smiths Industries, the UK conglomerate with interests
in aeronautics, defence systems and medical equipment, became the owners in
l977.
Steady growth, particularly over the past five years, has established the
Milngavie company in its position as a leading European ducting manufacturer.
It is now regarded as spearheading the growth of the entire Smiths ducting and
conduit division, which is represented by companies in the USA, Germany,
Switzerland and France.
Flexible Ducting's range of products has also continued to grow - a growth
further enhanced last year by the purchase of a range of products from a
competitor. While heating, ventilation and air conditioning remain among the
largest markets, the popular Thermaflex range can be found in HVAC systems in
hotels, aircraft, ships, offices and entire office blocks throughout the world.
The motor industry is another customer which takes a signficant part of the
output from Milngavie. Flexflyte Super is used in air intakes, heaters and
turbochargers. Underlining that established reputation for quality, Flexible
Ducting also supplies equipment to Rolls Royce, Lamborghini, Ferrari, Mercedes
Benz, and other top-end manufacturers.
Products for industrial use are manufactured for such widely varied uses as
carrying air, dust, fumes, cement powder, wood chippings and abrasive
substances including metal filings. Another expansion, in l990, was a venture
into the industrial hose market which followed on the acquisition of sole
European manufacturing and sales rights for an exclusive range of highly
flexible suction and discharge hoses from a Japanese company.
Known as Kanaline and a direct replacement for traditional rubber hose, it is
claimed to combine lightness and flexibility with a robust durability. It is
now widely used within the oil industry and in many other industries, including
processing, agriculture, chemicals and civil engineering.
A fourth area in which the Milngavie firm specialises, consumer durables, is
one in which marketing manager Mr Peter Samborek emphasises the paramount
importance of quality.
``Appliances in everyday use, such as hairdryers, tumble driers and vacuum
cleaners, require exceptionally high specification ducting to guarantee
durability,'' he said. ``European customers place great emphasis on quality and
demand that every piece of ducting is absolutely flawless. It is our policy to
meet these high standards as a matter of course.'' Strict quality control
procedures are in place at all times to ensure that every product leaving the
Flexible Ducting factory has been rigorously tested.
The range supplied in the consumer durables sector includes retractable hose
for use in upright vacuum cleaners produced by Electrolux, Hoover, Vax and
Dyson. High extension ratio hoses have also been introduced to allow these
companies to offer stair cleaning facilities on their machines.
A much praised facility offered to customers at Milngavie is an established
custom design department. Expert advice can be given on the requirements for
ducting or hose for specialised applications of every kind. This is a back-up
service backing a wide range of existing sales literature and published
guidance. It forms one more aspect of the ``Quality by Design'' motto and the
application behind it which has created the penetration of markets, both at
home and abroad, achieved by progresssive marketing by a strong sales network.
The ultimate proof is that even with the new major extension, the Milngavie
workforce is currently going flat-out to deal with demand.
</TEXT>
