<HEADLINE>Greenwood makes Samoans suffer</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>28</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974913714</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
England A 55,
Western Samoa 0
CENTRE Will Greenwood grabbed a hat trick as England A sent Western Samoa into
Saturday's Twickenham Test on the receiving end of a crushing whitewash at
Gateshead last night.
England A got the try count rolling as Gloucester flanker Richard West won a
lineout for Bath prop Kevin Yates to power through the gap. Bristol's Martin
Corry carried on the good work before Wasps scrum-half Andy Gomarsall darted
under the posts for full back Tim Stimpson to land the first of his six
conversions.
But the sluice gates in the Samoan defence were fully opened when Greenwood,
Andrew Blyth and wing Jim Naylor were all involved before the centre got the
first of his treble. Gloucester hooker Phil Greening burst through for a fine
try before Greenwood completed a break from outside-half Alex King by racing in
from halfway.
Saracens flanker Richard Hill charged over soon after the interval, then
Greenwood completed his hat-trick after a King interception. Gomarsall added
his second soon after, and Leicester prop Darren Garforth brought up the
half-century of points.
England A - T Stimpson (West Hartlepool); J Sleightholme (Bath), A Blyth (West
Hartlepool), W Greenwood (Harlequins), J Naylor (Orrell); A King (Bristol
University), A Gomarsall (Wasps); K Yates (Bath), P Greening (Gloucester), D
Garforth (Leicester), G Archer (Bristol), R West (Gloucester), M Corry
(Bristol), T Diprose (Saracens), captain, R Hill (Saracens).
Western Samoa - A Autagavaia; T Faaiuaso, S Leaega, K Tuigamala, F Fereti; C
Burnes, M Vaea; B Reidy, O Matauiau, G Latu, S Lemamea, M Birtwistle, captain,
L Taala, S Smith, M Iupeli.
